/*In HTML4, this is always the <html> element, since it is the highest-level ancestor of all other elements on the page. So, :root is identical to using the html as a selector, except that it has a higher specificity. This means that, in the following example, the styles specified using :root will override those specified using the html selector, even if the latter comes next in the style sheet. In document formats other than HTML, such as SVG and XML,  the :root pseudo-class can refer to another higher-level ancestor.*/  :root {     /* style the root element */ }  html {     /* style the root element */ }                 
